<h1>MA110 – 2019 Past Paper (Fully Solved)</h1>

<!-- QUESTION 1 -->
<div class="section">
<h2>Question 1</h2>

<h3>(a)(i)</h3>
<p>Let <b>A = {1, 2, 3}</b> and <b>B = {2, 4}</b>. Find <b>A × B</b>.</p>

<div class="math">
A × B = {(a, b) : a ∈ A, b ∈ B}
<br><br>
= {(1,2), (1,4), (2,2), (2,4), (3,2), (3,4)}
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: {(1,2), (1,4), (2,2), (2,4), (3,2), (3,4)}</p>

<hr>

<h3>(a)(ii)</h3>
<p>Prove that <b>(Aᶜ)ᶜ = A</b>.</p>

<div class="math">
Let x ∈ (Aᶜ)ᶜ  
<br>
⇒ x ∉ Aᶜ  
<br>
⇒ x ∈ A  
<br><br>
Hence (Aᶜ)ᶜ ⊆ A
<br><br>
Similarly, if x ∈ A ⇒ x ∉ Aᶜ ⇒ x ∈ (Aᶜ)ᶜ
</div>

<p class="answer">Therefore, (Aᶜ)ᶜ = A</p>

<hr>

<h3>(b)</h3>
<p>The operation ★ is defined as:  
<b>a ★ b = a + 8b</b></p>

<div class="math">
2 ★ 3 = 2 + 8(3) = 26  
<br>
(2 ★ 3) ★ 5 = 26 + 8(5) = 66
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: 66</p>

<hr>

<h3>(c)</h3>
<p>Find k if the remainder when <b>2x³ − 2kx² − 3x − 2</b> is divided by <b>x − 2</b> is 40.</p>

<div class="math">
By Remainder Theorem:
<br>
f(2) = 40
<br><br>
2(2³) − 2k(2²) − 3(2) − 2 = 40  
<br>
16 − 8k − 6 − 2 = 40  
<br>
8 − 8k = 40  
<br>
−8k = 32  
<br>
k = −4
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: k = −4</p>

<hr>

<h3>(d)</h3>
<p>Given that <b>g ∘ f(x) = x</b> and <b>g(x) = (x + 1)/(x − 1)</b>, find f(x).</p>

<div class="math">
Let y = f(x)
<br>
g(y) = (y + 1)/(y − 1) = x
<br><br>
x(y − 1) = y + 1  
<br>
xy − x = y + 1  
<br>
xy − y = x + 1  
<br>
y(x − 1) = x + 1  
<br>
y = (x + 1)/(x − 1)
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: f(x) = (x + 1)/(x − 1)</p>
</div>

<!-- QUESTION 2 -->
<div class="section">
<h2>Question 2</h2>

<h3>(a)</h3>
<p>Prove De Morgan’s Law: <b>(A ∪ B)ᶜ = Aᶜ ∩ Bᶜ</b></p>

<div class="math">
Let x ∈ (A ∪ B)ᶜ  
<br>
⇒ x ∉ A ∪ B  
<br>
⇒ x ∉ A and x ∉ B  
<br>
⇒ x ∈ Aᶜ and x ∈ Bᶜ  
<br>
⇒ x ∈ Aᶜ ∩ Bᶜ
</div>

<p class="answer">Hence proved.</p>

<hr>

<h3>(b)</h3>
<p>Solve |8x + 3| = |2x − 21|</p>

<div class="math">
Case 1: 8x + 3 = 2x − 21  
<br>
6x = −24 ⇒ x = −4  
<br><br>
Case 2: 8x + 3 = −(2x − 21)  
<br>
8x + 3 = −2x + 21  
<br>
10x = 18 ⇒ x = 9/5
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: x = −4 or x = 9/5</p>
</div>

<!-- QUESTION 3 -->
<div class="section">
<h2>Question 3</h2>

<h3>(a)</h3>
<p>Express 0.121212… as a fraction.</p>

<div class="math">
Let x = 0.121212…  
<br>
100x = 12.1212…  
<br>
100x − x = 12  
<br>
99x = 12  
<br>
x = 4/33
</div>

<p class="answer">Answer: 4/33</p>

<hr>

<h3>(b)</h3>
<p>Prove that √2 + √3 is irrational.</p>

<div class="math">
Assume √2 + √3 is rational.
<br>
Squaring gives: 5 + 2√6 is rational.
<br>
⇒ √6 is rational (contradiction).
</div>

<p class="answer">Hence √2 + √3 is irrational.</p>
</div>

<!-- QUESTION 4 -->
<div class="section">
<h2>Question 4</h2>

<h3>(a)</h3>
<p>Find the vertex and intercepts of f(x) = x² − 6x − 16</p>

<div class="math">
Vertex:
<br>
x = −b/2a = 6/2 = 3  
<br>
y = f(3) = −25  
<br><br>
Intercepts:
<br>
(x − 8)(x + 2) = 0  
<br>
x = 8, −2
</div>

<p class="answer">Vertex: (3, −25), Intercepts: (8,0), (−2,0)</p>
</div>

